'''point-of-purchase''' a place where a product or service may be bought or promoted, e.g. retail outlets, receptions, stations and airports.

'''point-of-purchase''', '''point-of-purchase advertising'''  a generic term for display units (e.g. retail display stands, showcases, interactive displays, literature dispensers, poster holders, sign holders etc.) used to merchandise specific goods and services, or as a vehicle for presenting point-of-sale advertising such as printed leaflets, posters, or audio-visual media.